==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bichromate
<hw>Bi*chro"mate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>chromate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
salt containing two parts of chromic acid to one of the other
ingredients; <as>as, potassium <ex>bichromate</ex></as>; -- called also
<altname>dichromate</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bichromatize</ent>⟦br⟧
